The Westfjords Way film is here! A route dedicated to all those that have explored this unique part of the world via bicycle. last September we biked the route and this summer we are launching the first-ever Westfjords Way Challenge — a five day Ultra Endurance Stage race around some of Iceland’s most remote and pristine wilderness. From June 28- July 3, riders will race a total of 930Km under endless sunlight through never ending fjords, world class gravel and multiple hot springs. 

The race, organized by @cyclingwestfjords , will have BIPOC scholarships available. For details and registration for this self supported race please follow @cyclingwestfjords for updates and to reserve your spot. 

Film by @thrainnko @visitwestfjords 

@fezzari_bicycles @icelandair 
@sramroad @infinitybikeseat

Proud to release this short film about my passion for wide angle lenses. Shot on location in Mallorca a few months back with Sony. It was a dream assignment to try and capture light in the Balearic Sea with a handful of incredible athletes. Working in these environments, especially when the moments are so finite with the weather, the light and the stamina - it reminds me what I love most about growing up as a sports photographer. I had seen this route years prior and dreamt of coming back and shooting it in perfect light. 

